documentation.text:
This project was built out of nostalgia for the early years of World of Warcraft
 Seeing how empty Azeroth is these days, I'm reminded of all the adventurers that logged off for the last time years ago
 The randomly generated descriptions in this contract evoke a sense of reflection on the lore behind each Forgotten Adventurer
@dev Sets the maximum amount mintable
@dev Sets the mint price in wei
@dev Emitted when an adventurer is generated and the initial request for randomness has been made
@dev Emitted in the fulfillRandomness callback function after randomness has been received from the VRF
@dev Emitted after randomness has been used to generate an adventurer and finalize minting
@dev Requirements for the Chainlink VRF
@dev Used to define a mapping between adventurer names and races

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

svgToImageURI(string).details: Encodes our SVG so that it's viewable as an NFT

params._svg: The SVG representing our Adventurer and their traits

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

price.details: Sets the mint price in wei

races.details: Used to define a mapping between adventurer names and races

create().notice: Requests a random number from the Chainlink VRF and creates a new token ID

finishMint(uint256).notice: Receives a random number from the Chainlink VRF and uses that to finish generating an adventurer

generateSVG(uint256).notice: Creates our image for the NFT

getClass(uint256).notice: Randomly chooses an adventurer's class using the pluckString() function

getLastSeen(uint256).notice: Randomly chooses an adventurer's last seen location using the pluckString() function

getLevel(uint256).notice: Randomly chooses an adventurer's level using output from the Chainlink VRF

getMaxAvailable().notice: Get the maximum number of NFT's available

getName(uint256).notice: Randomly chooses an adventurer's name using the pluckString() function

getRace(uint256).notice: Randomly chooses an adventurer's race using the pluckString() function

getTotalNFTsMintedSoFar().notice: Get total number of NFT's minted

withdraw().notice: Usable by the owner to withdraw funds from the contract

userdoc.notice: This project was built out of nostalgia for the early years of World of Warcraft Seeing how empty Azeroth is these days, I'm reminded of all the adventurers that logged off for the last time years ago The randomly generated descriptions in this contract evoke a sense of reflection on the lore behind each Forgotten Adventurer
